Docker Volume:-A Docker Volume is used to persist data even after a container is deleted.
Stored outside container
Managed by Docker
Why use Volume:- Because containers are temporary (ephemeral)
Volumes provide:-Data persistence if container deleted


Types of Storage
1. Named Volume
2. Bind Mount (Local Volume)
3. Anonymous Volume

----

docker volume create myvolume      # Create volume

docker volume ls                   # List volumes

docker volume inspect myvolume     # Inspect volume

docker volume rm myvolume          # Remove volume

docker volume prune                # Remove unused volumes

docker run -v myvolume:/data nginx # Mount named volume

docker run -v /host:/data nginx    # Bind mount

docker run -v /data nginx          # Anonymous volume
----


# 6. Use Named Volume

docker run -d \
--name nginx-c1 \
-v my-volume:/usr/share/nginx/html \
nginx

-----
# 7. Use Local Folder (Bind Mount)

docker run -d \
--name nginx-c1 \
-v $(pwd)/html:/usr/share/nginx/html \
nginx

or

docker run -d \
-v /home/ubuntu/html:/usr/share/nginx/html \
nginx
